The paper deals with program specifications in separation logic for concurrency, which is a topic related to logic and programming languages (cs.LO) as well as software engineering (cs.SE). The use of algebraic structures and state transition systems also suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and formal methods (cs.FL). Finally, the application of morphisms and simulations to facilitate proof reuse involves concepts from category theory and algebra, which could be relevant to data structures (cs.DS).
